cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper is about a large scale database of dynamic high-resolution 3D faces that can be used for face and facial expression recognition, as well as behavioural biometrics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests the category cs.MM (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the database in human-computer interaction (HCI), which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions the use of the database for learning blendshapes, which suggests the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the usefulness of the database for various applications, which suggests the category cs.LG (Learning).
